article.headline: Chattanooga 29, Presbyterian 13
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Bryan Fitzgerald rushed for 181 yards and two touchdowns to lead Chattanooga to a 29-13 victory over Presbyterian on Saturday. Fitzgerald, who had 22 carries, scored on a 15-yard run in the second quarter to give the Mocs (2-1) a 16-10 halftime lead. He capped the scoring with a 27-yard, fourth-quarter run. Chattanooga's B.J. Coleman was 16 of 29 for 224 yards and two touchdowns. He hit Chris Pitchford on a 3-yard scoring pass and threw a 20-yard touchdown to Terrance Davis, who finished with three catches for 76 yards. Ryan Consiglio led Chattanooga with 12 tackles, a sack and an interception that set up the Mocs' first field goal. Brandon Miley was 16 of 27 for 194 yards for Presbyterian (0-3). The Blue Hose led 10-3 on Trandon Dendy's 1-yard run before Coleman hit Pitchford to tie the score at 10.
